This paper focuses on the interpretability of recommender systems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the challenges of over-confidence and under-confidence in predictions, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the use of attention distribution for interpretability is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL).
